description:
In a story that spans Japan's history and future, and alludes to the haunting traditions of the Japanese Ghost story, Kabuki: Circle of Blood touches on the interdependence between organized crime and politics in Japan.

Kabuki Volume 1: Circle of Blood is Mack's first published Kabuki story. It was completed and released at age 21, while he was in college, and turned in for his senior writing thesis.

description: Fun√©railles has been sent away to a military bootcamp. His mother hopes he will not survive this, but Fun√©railles overcomes all difficulties and succeeds in uniting his group into a band of brothers (and sisters). Meanwhile Scipio is sent to an upperclass institution for his education. Like Pretorius he is a rebel, who defies all authority. He hates his mother for what she has done to his father and secretly tries to stay in contact with his brother. Their mother meanwhile slowly becomes insane, because she can not overcome the grief and the guilt for the death of her husband.

description:
76 pages of gamma-charged action!

The Avengers join the action as a wounded Hulk fights a titanic battle against the resurrected Abomination! By Mark Waid and Mark Bagley!

The original X-Men clash with the Hulk for the first time! Classic action from Roy Thomas and Sal Buscema!

Featuring material first printed in Hulk #3-4, She-Hulk #2 and X-Men #66.
